  "texts": [
    "Despite its stated goal of protecting fundamental rights including data protection, the structure of the AI Act follows product safety law paramenters and as such has a fundamentally different approach than legal frameworks aimed at protecting fundamental rights, as found in the GDPR.",
    "The AI Act does establish certain obligations for high-risk AI-systems such as data governance, transparency requirements and standards for human oversight.",
    "However, these provisions do not address the privacy and data protection of users.",
    "This leaves a great need for legal regulation.",
    "https://doi.org/10.1017/cfl.2024.2 Published online by Cambridge University Press"
  ],
